text.__SUMMARY__: Acer sycopseoides is an Asian species of maple. It is native to China (Guangxi, Guizhou, Yunnan).Acer sycopseoides is a small tree up to 6 meters tall with gray bark. Leaves are non-compound, up to 8 cm wide and 4 cm across, thick and leathery, with a 1-2 short, shallow lobes along the edges.
